# Branch Naming Conventions

## Format

```
<type>/<short-description>
```

Include a ticket ID when available: `<type>/<TICKET-ID>-<short-description>`

## Allowed Prefixes

| Prefix | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `feature/` | New features, enhancements |
| `fix/` | Bug fixes |
| `hotfix/` | Urgent production fixes |
| `refactor/` | Refactoring without behavior change |
| `chore/` | Build, tooling, dependencies, config |
| `docs/` | Documentation only |
| `test/` | Adding or updating tests |
| `release/` | Release preparation |

## Rules

1. Lowercase only
2. Use hyphens (`-`) between words (kebab-case)
3. Keep under ~50 characters total
4. Use present tense (`add-login`, not `added-login`)
5. Letters, numbers, and hyphens only in the description part
6. Include ticket ID when applicable (e.g. `feature/EDIEL-42-add-jwt-auth`)

## Examples

```
feature/add-user-dashboard
feature/jwt-auth
fix/login-redirect-loop
hotfix/payment-validation-crash
refactor/extract-auth-service
chore/update-dependencies
docs/api-endpoints
feature/EDIEL-42-add-jwt-auth
```

## Anti-patterns

- `my-branch`, `test`, `fix` -- too vague, always describe the change
- `Feature_Add_Login` -- use lowercase kebab-case, not PascalCase or underscores
- `fix/bug` -- describe what the fix addresses
- `feature/add-login-and-registration-and-password-reset` -- too long; split into separate branches

## Validation Regex

Branch names must match: `^(feature|fix|hotfix|refactor|chore|docs|test|release)/[a-z0-9-]+$`
